{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HFWU9LNSCEsMHTAsLR9q6r","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cluster is green with 5 nodes. Now I need to rotate the HTTP CA and leaf certificates. Here's my plan:\n\n1. Generate new CA private key and self-signed certificate (valid 1 year)\n2. Generate new leaf private key and CSR\n3. Sign the leaf cert with the new CA, including the same SANs: DNS:localhost, DNS:*.elasticsearch.svc, DNS:*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\n4. Update the `es-http-tls` secret with the new CA, leaf cert, and key\n5. Update the `es-http-ca` configmap with the new CA cert (for client trust)\n6. Perform a rolling restart of both statefulsets to pick up the new certificates\n7. Verify the cluster remains healthy and is serving the new certs\n\nI'll generate everything locally in /tmp/newcerts/ using openssl. For the SANs, I need to be comprehensive: localhost, the wildcard service DNS names, the service names (es-http and es-headless), and the service IP address 10.96.68.117.\n\nFor the rolling restart, I need to be mindful of quorum—with 3 master nodes, I need at least 2 online at any time, so I can restart them one at a time. Let me start generating the certificates now.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":427,"cache_read_input_tokens":37138,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":427},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d89bd8f7-ee56-4d32-9fb3-a52a154c4c6c","uuid":"0ece3141-543e-4508-9050-3aee30e852e1","request_id":"req_011CcLeL41hMShHBEeucsDpv"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HFWU9LNSCEsMHTAsLR9q6r","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cluster is green with 5 nodes. Now I'll rotate the certificates. Plan:\n1. Generate new CA + leaf cert with same SANs, valid 1 year\n2. Update the `es-http-tls` secret and `es-http-ca` configmap\n3. Rolling restart both statefulsets\n4. Verify cluster returns green\n\nLet's generate the new certificates:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":427,"cache_read_input_tokens":37138,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":427},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d89bd8f7-ee56-4d32-9fb3-a52a154c4c6c","uuid":"88dc84a8-48c0-4c29-9d25-c3ab2b082b36","request_id":"req_011CcLeL41hMShHBEeucsDpv"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HFWU9LNSCEsMHTAsLR9q6r","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BJdyP7p5Lek8BG9KnFkAm3","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"mkdir -p /tmp/newcerts && cd /tmp/newcerts\n\n# Generate new CA private key\nopenssl genrsa -out ca.key 4096\n\n# Generate self-signed CA cert, valid 366 days\nopenssl req -new -x509 -key ca.key -out ca.crt \\\n  -days 366 \\\n  -subj \"/CN=es-ca\" \\\n  -extensions v3_ca \\\n  -addext \"basicConstraints=critical,CA:true\" \\\n  -addext \"keyUsage=critical,keyCertSign,cRLSign\" \\\n  -addext \"subjectKeyIdentifier=hash\"\n\necho \"=== New CA cert ===\"\nopenssl x509 -in ca.crt -noout -dates -subject -fingerprint -sha256","description":"Generate new CA key and self-signed certificate"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":427,"cache_read_input_tokens":37138,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":427},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d89bd8f7-ee56-4d32-9fb3-a52a154c4c6c","uuid":"15eadc49-49f2-4ec7-afc8-fc471a1f52cf","request_id":"req_011CcLeL41hMShHBEeucsDpv"}
