{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Hqx5JDjsybMwRpN7xZnqa1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So now:\n- es-0 is 0/1 Running (was restarted by the background task, took it 2m36s to appear as Running but not Ready yet)\n- es-1 is 0/1 Running (5m9s)\n- es-2 is 0/1 Running (7m13s)\n- es-data-0 is 1/1 Running (16m) - still on old certs\n- es-data-1 is 1/1 Running (16m) - still on old certs\n\nAll three master nodes are now using the new certs but they can't form a cluster with the data nodes that have old certs.\nThe fix is to create a combined CA bundle with both old and new CAs, update the secret with this combined CA plus the new leaf cert and key, then restart the data nodes so they can communicate with both the old and new cert nodes, followed by restarting the master nodes again with the combined CA. So when the data nodes restart with the combined CA and new leaf cert, both sides can verify each other: the masters will accept the data nodes' new certs (signed by the new CA they trust), and the data nodes will accept the masters' new certs (since they now trust both old and new CAs). The next step is to create that combined CA, update the secret with it alongside the new leaf cert and key, then restart the data nodes. with new certs) and wait for them to come back up. Since the cluster is already broken with the masters unable to communicate with the data nodes, restarting both data nodes simultaneously shouldn't cause additional issues.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4464,"cache_read_input_tokens":44035,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4464},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d89bd8f7-ee56-4d32-9fb3-a52a154c4c6c","u